# Git Commit Discipline

- When the user asks for commits, make them atomic: one logical change per commit, with no unrelated files mixed in.
- Stage only files that belong to the same change. Do not bundle cleanup, refactors, generated files, and feature work together unless they are inseparable parts of one logical change.
- Prefer small, reviewable commits with clear intent and commit messages in English that explain the purpose of the change.
- Do not add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any other Cursor mention to commit messages.
- Follow normal safe git workflow: inspect status/diff before committing, avoid destructive git operations, and do not rewrite published history unless the user explicitly asks.
- Do not push, force-push, or create remote side effects unless the user explicitly asks for that step.
